    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is offset by the multi-laboratory experimental dataset, the specimen-specific parameterisation of all 11 FEA instances, and the conservative E/uval results across all QoIs. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level conclusion that the FEA framework reliably predicts ASTM F1717 compression-bending behaviour of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct within the stated acceptance bounds.",
